SIMPLE: damnable
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Damnable
<hw>Dam"na*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>damnabilis</ets>, fr. <ets>damnare</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>damnable</ets>. See <er>Damn</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Liable
to damnation; deserving, or for which one deserves, to be damned; of a
damning nature.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A creature unprepared unmeet for death,⟦br⟧
And to transport him in the mind he is,⟦br⟧
Were <qex>damnable</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Odious; pernicious; detestable.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Begin, murderer; . . . leave thy <qex>damnable</qex> faces.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Damnableness</ent>⟦br⟧
